            <div class="svc-text-col">
              <div class="svc-detail-label">Chinese and Japanese Acupuncture</div>
              <div class="svc-detail-text">Acupuncture increases the body's release of natural painkillers in the pain pathways of both the spinal cord and brain, modifying the way pain signals are received. Japanese Acupuncture specifically uses reflective points to release Active and Latent Trigger Points, reducing structural imbalance throughout the body. Beyond pain relief, it has positive effects on digestion, stress, sleep, and overall function. Dr. Saad is licensed from both USJ Lebanon and Tianjin TCM University, China.</div>
